
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `gprofng` yek abzar baraye tahlil va behینه سازی barname-ha ast. In dastoor barname-haye shoma ra monitor mikonad ta bebinad kodam bakhsh-ha bishtarin zaman ra masraf mikonand. Ba estefade az `gprofng`, shoma mitavanid noghat-e gheyre-bahrevar ra peyda konid va barname-ye khod ra behtar konid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `gprofng collect` --> 💾 Etela'at profile-ra jam'avari mikonad. Bayad qabl az ejraye barname estefade shavad.
    🔹 `gprofng display` --> 📊 Etela'at profile-ra namayesh midahad.
    🔹 `gprofng report`  --> 📝 Gozaresh-e kamele profile-ra misazad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ gprofng collect ./myprogram

    🔹 Etela'at profile az barname-ye `myprogram` jam'avari mikonad.

    $ gprofng display

    🔹 Etela'at profile-ra dar terminal namayesh midahad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ gprofng collect ./myprogram; ./myprogram; gprofng display

    🔹 Avval etela'at profile jam'avari mishavad, sepas barname ejra mishavad, va dar akhar etela'at profile namayesh dade mishavad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `gprofng` command is a tool for profiling and optimizing programs. It monitors your programs to see which parts consume the most time. By using `gprofng`, you can identify bottlenecks and improve your program's performance.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `gprofng collect` --> 💾 Collects profiling data. Must be used before running the program.
    🔹 `gprofng display` --> 📊 Displays profiling data.
    🔹 `gprofng report`  --> 📝 Generates a full profiling report.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ gprofng collect ./myprogram

    🔹 Collects profiling data from the `myprogram` program.

    $ gprofng display

    🔹 Displays the profiling data in the terminal.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ gprofng collect ./myprogram; ./myprogram; gprofng display

    🔹 First, profiling data is collected, then the program is executed, and finally, the profiling data is displayed.
